p4
VThe Tiruchirapalli Tamil Isai Sangam celebrated its 59 {+t} {+h} monthly music festival with Lavanya Vaidyanathan's vocal recital held at the Tamil Sangam premises in Tiruchi.Nellai Ravindran on the violin, Guru Raghavendra on the mridangam and Malaikottai Deenadayalan on the morsing rendered able assistance to her.L.N. Lakshmanan, president, Tiruchirapalli Tamil Isai Sangam, presided over the function. M. Sellappan, proprietor, Palaniappa Brothers Book Stall, who was the chief guest, traced the history of Tamil isai and how it has achieved unique distinction in the present scenario.He also recalled the vital role played by the Muthiah Chettiar family in promoting Tamil isai. He appealed for steps to set up a separate premises for the Tamil Isai Sangam such as the ones in Chennai and Madurai.Rangarajan, secretary of the Tamil Isai Sangam, G.R. Venugopal of Radhakrishna Jewellery, the sponsor of the programme, and others offered felicitations.
